<FIRST>u a AM-TexasNursingFire     12-25 0128</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Texas Nursing Fire,0131</SECOND>
<HEAD>Three Injured in Fire At Texas Nursing Home</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Retirement Home Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire broke out at a nursing home
Sunday, injuring three people and forcing 60 others to move into
different rooms, officials said.
   The blaze started at 7:35 a.m. Firefighters confined the fire to
one room, but many others were damaged by smoke and water used to
extinguished the blaze.
   Two residents and a firefighter were treated for smoke
inhalation at Arlington Memorial Hospital and released.
   ``We feel fortunate there were no other injuries, and the Fire
Department was quick enough to contain the fire,'' said Gary
Anderson, vice president of operations for the nursing home.
   The cause of the fire has not been determined, officials said.
</TEXT>
