<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PANAMA CITY, Panama (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U.S. troops and armored vehicles
ringed the Vatican Embassy early today after deposed strongman Gen.
Manuel Antonio Noriega escaped a massive search, took refuge and
asked for asylum.
   About 40 soldiers kept watch in the pre-dawn darkness as a
Blackhawk helicopter, its running lights turned off, landed several
times across the street from the embassy, then took off.
   A reporter said he did not see the chopper pick up or discharge
anyone.
   An official at the Vatican said the nunciature could try to turn
Noriega over to the new government or arrange for safe passage to
another country but not put him in the hands of the United States,
